# Git Workflow Rules

## Branch Strategy

All development work MUST follow this workflow:

1. **Always work on `develop` branch locally**
   - Never make changes directly on `main`
   - Switch to develop before starting any work: `git checkout develop`

2. **Push to `develop` first**
   - All commits go to develop first: `git push origin develop`
   - This deploys to dev.4tango.com for testing

3. **Merge to `main` only after testing on develop**
   - Once changes are verified on dev.4tango.com
   - Merge develop into main: `git checkout main && git merge develop`
   - Push to main: `git push origin main`
   - This deploys to production (4tango.com)

## Workflow Commands

```bash
# Start work (always from develop)
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop

# Make changes and commit
git add <files>
git commit -m "Description"

# Push to develop first
git push origin develop

# After testing on dev.4tango.com, merge to main
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git merge develop
git push origin main

# Return to develop for next task
git checkout develop
```

## Rules

- NEVER push directly to main without going through develop first
- NEVER force push to main
- Always test on dev.4tango.com before merging to main
- Keep develop and main in sync after production deployments
